---
import "../styles/global.css";
import Header from "../components/Header/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer/Footer.astro";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <title>Workshops | Broken Duck Studio</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  </head>

  <body>
    <Header />

    <main class="container" style="padding: 4rem 1.5rem; max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <h1 style="font-size: 2.25rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Sunday Workshops</h1>

      <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; color: #ccc; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
        Every Sunday from 1pm to 4pm, Broken Duck Studio hosts a members-only workshop. These sessions are designed to help creators grow — whether you’re refining your lighting setup, planning a new video series, or troubleshooting your upload workflow.
      </p>

      <p style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
        Workshops are structured but flexible. Topics rotate weekly and are often led by studio members themselves. Some weeks might focus on thumbnails or scripting, others might split into breakout rooms for live editing, feedback, or gear-specific tutorials.
      </p>

      <p style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
        These sessions are a chance to share ideas, get support, and move your channel forward — with people who get it. We keep them practical, small, and relevant to creators in the room.
      </p>

      <p style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
        The final Sunday of every month is reserved for a public <a href="/events" style="color: var(--color-theme); text-decoration: underline;">studio event</a>, open to the wider creative community in Chiang Mai.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-top: 3rem;">How to Join</h2>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
        All members are welcome to attend. Just show up on time. No need to book ahead. If you’re interested in hosting a session or suggesting a topic, you can propose ideas through the member portal once it launches.
      </p>
    </main>

    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>
